> One of my customers is looking to let his '75 Automatic bus go. It has a
> very unique wheelchair access conversion. It is for transporting a
> wheelchair bound passenger only. It does not have hand controls. The floor
> has been lowered and the sliding door modified for a wheelchair ramp. It
> also has a wheelchair alcove and restraints built in. It was done very
> nicely as far as I can tell and most of the original hardware is still
> there. The bus is worth saving just for its uniqueness and the potential to
> help a disabled person have one cool ride.
